<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_cʼærna" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><form type="lemma"><orth>cʼærna</orth><lang/></form><sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>веснущатый</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>freckled</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>пятнистый</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>spotted</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>веснушка</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>freckle</q></cit></sense></sense><re><form type="lemma"><orth>cʼærna karkæ</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>рябая курица</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>speckled hen</q></cit></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>cærnagun</orth></form><sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>рябой</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>specky</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>веснущатый</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>freckled</q></cit></sense></sense></re><etym xml:lang="ru">Примыкает к <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>cʼreli</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w>č’rela</w><gloss><q>пестрый</q></gloss></mentioned>,  через ступени %ičʼrela → *cʼærla → cʼærna%i, ср. звуковые отношения <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>cxrila</w></mentioned> → ос. <xr><ref target="#entry_syxyrna"/></xr> ‘решето’. Огласовка %iæ%i в осетинском позволяет рассматривать это слово как „мегрелизм“, хотя в современном мегрельском мы имеем, как и в грузинском, <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>čʼreli</w></mentioned>, а не %i*čʼrali%i (ср. „мегрельскую“ огласовку в %ikær%i-, <xr><ref target="#entry_cæxær"/><ref target="#entry_ænʒalm"/><ref target="#entry_car"/></xr>). Грузинское слово, со своей стороны, можно поставить в связь с некоторыми словами других кавказских языков: <mentioned xml:lang="lez"><lang/><w>cʼarù</w><gloss><q>пестрый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="tab"><lang/><w>cʼar-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/><w>čar-</w></mentioned> id.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope>526</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It relates to <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>cʼreli</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w>č’rela</w><gloss><q>mottle</q></gloss></mentioned>,  through the following steps: %ičʼrela → *cʼærla → cʼærna%i, cf. sound relations <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>cxrila</w></mentioned> → Ossetic. <xr><ref target="#entry_syxyrna"/></xr> ‘sieve’. The vocalization %iæ%i in Ossetic let consider this word as a “Mingrelism”, although in modern Mingrelian, as well as in Georgian, we have <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>čʼreli</w></mentioned>, and not %i*čʼrali%i (cf. “Mingrelian” vocalization in %ikær%i-, <xr><ref target="#entry_cæxær"/><ref target="#entry_ænʒalm"/><ref target="#entry_car"/></xr>). The Georgian word, for its part, can be related to some words of other Caucasian languages: <mentioned xml:lang="lez"><lang/><w>cʼarù</w><gloss><q>mottle</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="tab"><lang/><w>cʼar-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/><w>čar-</w></mentioned> id.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_ОЯФ_I"><biblScope>526</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry>